# Backend API Rules

- Keep endpoint style RESTful and response shape consistent.
- Always return actionable error messages in `message`.
- Protect sensitive routes with `authRequired` and role checks.
- Use parameterized queries only; never build raw SQL with string concat.
- Preserve backward compatibility for active endpoints unless user asks otherwise.
- Keep business calculations explicit and easy to audit.
